//Method : Method Description
1> length() : Returns the total number of characters present in the string
2> charAt(int index) : Returns the character at given index
3> equals(another_string) : Checks if both strings being compared have same value  (case sensitive).
                            Returns boolean value
4> equalsIgnoreCase(another_string) : Checks if both strings being compared have same value (case insensitive). 
                                      Returns boolean value
5> compareTo(another_string) : Checks the strings lexographically (case sensitive).
                              Returns 0 - Both are equal
                              Returns -ve - string lesser than another_string
                              Returns +ve - string greater than another_string
6> compareToIgnoreCase(another_string) : Same as compareTo() (case insensitive).
7> contains(charSequence S) : Checks if substring S exists
8> indexOf(String S) : First occurence of substring S's index
9> lastIndexOf(String S) : Last occurence of substring S's index
10> startsWith(String prefix) : Checks beginning of string is prefix.
11> endsWith(String suffix) : Checks ending of string is suffix.
12> toUpperCase() : Converts string to uppercase
13> toLowerCase() : Converts string to lowercase
14> trim() : Removes leading and trailing spaces
15> replace(char old, char new) : Replaces old characters with new character in string
16> replaceAll(String regex, String replacement) : Regular expression present is the string is replaced by the substring (replacement)
17> replaceFirst(String regex, String replacement) : Same as replaceAll() but only the first match is replaced
18> substring(int begin) : Extracts parts of string starting from the index begin
19> substring(int begin, int end) : Extracts part of string from index begin to index end-1
20> split(String regex) : Splits string into Array
21> join(CharSequenxe delimiter, elements) : Joins multiple strings
22> toCharArray() : Converts string to character array.
23> valueOf( any type) : Converts any type input to string
25> isEpmpty() : Checks if string is empty
26> isBlank() : Checks if string is empty and whitespace
27> concat(String str) : Joins two strings
28> intern() : Moves string refernce to string pool
29> format(String format, args) : Same working as printf in C
30> matches(String regex) : Check if string matches the pattern
